imagine we find a bug on an application,
but we don't know witch commit create this bug!
we can not check out on every commit to find it! (we can have thousands of commits)

BISECT
bisect command is powerful tools to make binary search on commits,
we introduce a bad commit (has bug) as end of the range,
we introduce a good commit (has not the bug) as beginning of the range.

1.git bisect start

2.git bisect bad    //the current commit (last commit) is the bad commit

3.git bisect good 01cc4bd  //introduce first commit as good commit

Note: now head is detached from branch
      git put it on middle of the range,
      the working directory is based on this commit
      so we run the app and check the bug.
      then we can set new bad & good commit until we
      find the commit has bug!

